9 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Manufacturer liability. (1) The manufacturer of a device is subject to
10 civil liability if:
11 (a) the device is activated in the state;
12 (b) the device does not enable a filter that complies with the requirements provided in [section 2]
13 on activation; and
14 (c) a minor accesses obscene content on the device.
15 (2) Notwithstanding subsection (1), this section does not apply to a manufacturer that makes a
16 good faith effort to provide a device that automatically enables a filter as required by [section 2] on activation of
17 the device in the state.
18 (3) Nothing in [sections 1 through 6 5]:
19 (a) applies to a device manufactured before [the effective date of this act]; or
20 (b) creates a cause of action against the retailer of a device.
21
22 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Individual liability. (1) A person WHO IS NOT A MINOR may be liable in a
23 civil and criminal action if the person intentionally enables the password to remove the filter on a device in the
24 possession of a minor and the minor accesses obscene content on the device.
25 (2) This section does not apply to the parent or legal guardian of a minor.
26
